					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956#post-4769411</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956/scp-5137#post-4769411</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 07 Sep 2020 13:48:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zander Lassiter</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6355729</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Why did Tom's skin decide to make more friends? Why did it think that one freind wasn't enough to make sure the man wouldn't be alone. I think the change in behavior needs a trigger.<br /> I found a couple grammar errors that can easily be fixed.</p> <blockquote> <p>PoI-5137: Oh, right. It says that I need to state your purpose. I… I need you to be my friend so I wouldn't be alone anymore. Like before. Does that sound good?<br /> {After a while, the man falls asleep. As he does so, SCP-5137-1 detaches from him. It crawls up the wall, into the ceiling and then out of the bedroom window.}</p> </blockquote> <p>wouldn't should be won't because the rest of the sentence is present tense, and Tom's skin crawls on to the ceiling not into it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956#post-4766194</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956/scp-5137#post-4766194</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 03 Sep 2020 17:58:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NotCity</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6773014</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I’m gonna novote this one. The concept and execution aren’t <em>bad</em>, but nothing really stuck out to me or caught my attention for too long. Aside from <em>ooh, scary skin monsters</em> this was just another monkey’s paw that didn’t build on anything new.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956#post-4765845</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13695956/scp-5137#post-4765845</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 03 Sep 2020 09:31:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Grigori Karpin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558017</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I don’t mind the predictability, because maybe the journey would be worth it. But I found no emotional connection to Gerry or his troubles.</p> <p>Honestly what turned me off is just how heavy the video log is in exposition, it’s clearly explaining the way he learned how to do this to the reader. I have a hard time buying that someone would continue making video journals like this. It would be one thing if he was recording it for posterity, but it’s just supposed to be a therapy technique.</p> <p>It’s a no vote for me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
